: 11px; padding: 0px;">HTML page structure:</h1><h1 style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(74, 74, 74); font-size: 20px; text-align: left; font-weight: 500; margin: 11px; padding: 0px;">&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;:&nbsp;This is the document type declaration (not technically a tag). It declares a document as being an HTML document. The doctype declaration is not case-sensitive.&lt;html&gt;:&nbsp;This is called the HTML root element. All other elements are contained within it.</h1><a href="http://localhost:8000/article?title=What%27s%20New%20in%20The%20latest%20Version%20of%20HTML?%20-%20HTML5" style="min-width: 64px; box-sizing: border-box; cursor: pointer; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-weight: 500; line-height: 1.75; border-radius: 4px; letter-spacing: 0.02857em; text-transform: uppercase; text-decoration: none; display: inline-block; text-align: center; font-size: 0.8125rem; padding: 4px 5px; box-shadow: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.2) 0px 3px 1px -2px, rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.14) 0px 2px 2px 0px, rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.12) 0px 1px 5px 0px; background-color: rgb(63, 81, 181); color: rgb(255, 255, 255); border: none;">SEE HTML5</a></div></div>',
