round-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(8, 255, 0); font-size: 29px; text-align: left; font-weight: 500; margin: 11px; padding: 0px;">Separating Design From Content:</h1><h1 style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(74, 74, 74); font-size: 20px; text-align: left; font-weight: 500; margin: 11px; padding: 0px;">Along with strongly encouraging semantic (meaningful) markup, the HTML5 specification strongly&nbsp;discourages&nbsp;non-meaningful markup ‚Äî markup intended only to tell the browser how to display things. This includes things like:declaring fonts and text colorssetting text alignment or justificationplacing borders on tablesdefining how text wraps around images</h1></div></div>',
